      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">You must check all measurements and calibrate as needed.
Take extra care to calibrate the transformer and the output current:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Transformer output voltage calibration: The characteristics
of the output transformer must be compensated to guarantee the 1%
output accuracy independent of the load.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Output current calibration: For a correct indication of the
load percentage and for the correct detection of an overload situation
and the transformer compensation.</p>
               </li>
            </ul>
         </p>
      </section>
