      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Transformer Output Voltage Calibration</title>
         <p class="- topic/p ">The
transformer is feedforward controlled. This means that the output
on the secondary side of the transformer is calculated based on the
actual measured current and compensated based on a stored characteristic
of the output transformer. The second regulator is the feedback controlled
outer control loop. This control loop is very slow and compensates
slow changes (temperature, ageing etc) to guarantee the 1% output
voltage tolerance. The transformer output voltage can be configured
as follows.<ol class="- topic/ol ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Set the UPS system in ‘standby state’. </p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Disable the outer control loop via the service port menu <menucascade class="+ topic/ph ui-d/menucascade ">
                        <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">System calibration</uicontrol>
                        <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">System test function</uicontrol>
                        <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Disable output transformer compensation</uicontrol>
                     </menucascade>.<note class="- topic/note ">Type two characters in: To activate function
two type in “02”.</note>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">After disabling the outer control loop, the system can be set
on. Configure the settings for the transformer output voltage as per
the table. If there is only resistive load available the 140% must
interpolated or the battery must be applied to help the input. Be
sure that the output current is already calibrated, so that the load
percentage is displayed correctly:<table outputclass="font:10" pgwide="1" class="- topic/table ">
