L12 / L1-N<fn class="- topic/fn ">Output voltage x 10</fn>
                        </entry>
                     </row>
                     <row class="- topic/row ">
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">399</entry>
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">Calibration OutVoltage
L23 / L1-N</entry>
                     </row>
                     <row class="- topic/row ">
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">400</entry>
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">Calibration OutVoltage L31 / L1-N</entry>
                     </row>
                  </tbody>
               </tgroup>
            </table>Three phase systems have standard values of 2080, 4800 and
6000 with 1:1 transformer. With all different transformers values
from 1000 to 7000 (100V to 700V) are possible. The outer control loop
is activated 5 seconds after turning on the system to avoid regulation
during startup ramp of output voltage. Too low voltages can be set
higher if the value in the outer control loop is set a bit higher.</p>
      </section>
